[[File:Leaping sturgeon detail.png|left|150px]]
The '''leaping sturgeon''' is a fish which requires 70 [[Fishing]], 45 [[Strength]], and 45 [[Agility]] to be caught, providing 80 Fishing experience, 7 Strength experience, and 7 Agility experience. It can be caught at [[Otto's Grotto]] or [[Mount Quidamortem]] with a [[barbarian rod]] and suitable bait after starting [[Barbarian Training]].

While it cannot be cooked, leaping sturgeon can be gutted with a [[knife]], providing a chance of receiving [[caviar]] and 15 [[Cooking]] experience, and may also produce [[fish offcuts]]. There's a 1/80 (1.25%) chance of receiving caviar with level 1 Cooking, and 100% chance at level 80, scaling in-between.{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/986534256724856832|date=18 April 2018|quote=Sturgeon: 1/80 at level 1, 100% at level 80. If that roll passes, 5/6 of offcuts with it.|archiveurl=https://archive.is/VNZWl|archivedate=29 May 2020}} If the player successfully receives caviar, they will be rewarded with 15 [[Cooking]] experience and a 5/6 chance of receiving fish offcuts as well. This is the only leaping fish to give [[caviar]] (which is sturgeon roe).

